This curious tale, while it contains many statements that are inaccurate, seems in its main features to have been founded upon fact, and supplies the infor- mation which is required to identify the ac- counts ofAdamnan and the Annals. It states that Congal Claen, the prime mover of the ex- pedition, was maternal grandson of Eochaidh Buidhe, and consequently that Domhnall Breac was his uncle. Thu, flying to Alba, he pre- sented himself at his grandfather’s court of Dun Monaidh (p. 46), at Sliabh Monaidh (p. 56).
